tweet: But just imagine if Dems went all in on #CancelRent and stuck to it or 5 months. If this was Trump‚Äôs response to that, he‚Äôd get criticized for some half ass bullshit, which it is. But now it‚Äôs the best we‚Äôve got

name: Pete üî•#CancelRentüî• Harrison
tweet: So is this cynical politics? Yeah. The contradiction of such a massive fed action based on covid response from an admin and agency that has downplayed it despite 185k deaths is mind blowing. But is it good politics? Oh hell yeah

name: Pete üî•#CancelRentüî• Harrison
tweet: Now they get to play defense in swing state cities against Trump who ‚Äúdid more for renters‚Äù than any Dem. Expecting Trump to be an evil plutocrat when he‚Äôs down in the polls was always wishful thinking. But Dems stumbled around on bullshit half measures like always and got burnt

name: Pete üî•#CancelRentüî• Harrison
tweet: One thing I don‚Äôt expect is the challenge to come from Dems. Leadership could have supported something like this, or better like #cancelrent and could have put it into CARES act when they had leverage but they didn‚Äôt.

name: Pete üî•#CancelRentüî• Harrison
tweet: The other Q is the basic legality of the action. This isn‚Äôt an executive order and though it lists CDC‚Äôs emergency powers in support, I have no idea how this works. I‚Äôd defer to anyone with more legal knowledge but this will get challenged somewhere so what comparisons exist?

name: Pete üî•#CancelRentüî• Harrison
tweet: This obviously just kicks the problem down the road. Either to a re-elected Trump who doesn‚Äôt care about evicting people at that point or a Biden admin that inherits a bomb going off. This is some scary shit but we already knew that

name: Pete üî•#CancelRentüî• Harrison
tweet: Much has already been said that it still obligates homerenters to pay full obligation. This is the main half measure. That‚Äôs never going to happen for millions of people. Not the CDC‚Äôs problem but the ‚Äúpartial payment‚Äù requirement leaves a lot of push back for landlords too

name: Pete üî•#CancelRentüî• Harrison
tweet: Start with the certification process. It suggests that landlords can‚Äôt challenge it but I don‚Äôt see clarity there or penalties if they do. Also seeing that normal fees and penalties can still be assessed. Abuse is very likely in this confusion.  Many tenants won‚Äôt hear about it

name: Pete üî•#CancelRentüî• Harrison
tweet: As health policy it‚Äôs overdue but as housing policy it is a half measure.  But damn it‚Äôs an important one for a lot of homerenters right now. The income requirements are shockingly broad which is good but the hardship requirements are vague and ripe for landlord abuse
